laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive to egg white, egg yolk, ovomucoid, wheat flour, barley flour, Dermatophagoides pteronyssinus, D. farinae, G. fusca, L. destructor, T. putrescentiae, cockroach; negative to pollen, molds, cat and dog dander, canary and pigeon feathers, ovalbumin, and rye flour.

1142 kU/l. IgE antibodies were detected to egg white (2.07 kU/l), egg yolk (0.86), ovomucoid (2.26), wheat flour (3.21), barley flour (1.95), alpha-amylase (0.39), lysozyme (2.05), D. pteronyssinus (5.60), D. farinae (5.48), L. destructor (3.70), and T. putrescentiae (5.58); negative to ovalbumin and to canary and pigeon feathers.
FVC of 105%, FEV1 of 94%, FEV1/FVC of 93%, FEF25-75 of 64%.
Elicited an early asthmatic response (22% fall in FEV1 in 10 min).
Elicited an early asthmatic response (24% fall in FEV1 in 20 min).
